P11. Painters Eleven: The Wild Ones of Canadian Art

NOWELL, Iris

Published by Douglas & McIntyre, Vancouver, 2010

ISBN 10: 1553655907 / ISBN 13: 9781553655909

Used / Hardcover Signed

Quantity: 1 available

Hardcover. Condition: Fine. xxxvii, 346 p. 29 cm. Colour illustrations throughout. Slight spine lean. Signed by author on title page. Also known as Painters 11 or P11, Painters Eleven was a group of abstract artists active in Canada between 1953 and 1960. Associated with the Abstract Expressionist movement, the group, and this book, consist of Ontario painters Jack Bush, Oscar Cahén, Hortense Gordon, Tom Hodgson, Alexandra Luke, Jock Macdonald, Ray Mead, Kazuo Nakamura, William Ronald, Harold Town and Walter Yarwood.
